RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 19000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANTHONY'S ROCKET chased in the five path, was under right handed encouragement in the two path midway around the turn, angled out to the six path while rallying into the final furlong, and drew past the inner pacesetter in the final strides. GARY'S FLYING LION set the pace in the three path, kicked away after a right handed cue turning into the stretch, but began to shorten stride going into the final sixteenth, and was caught late by a surging outer foe to place. REDISUR rated in the two path, was driven from the rail around the turn, and mildly stayed on from the two path in the stretch for show. CALLIHOO prompted the pace in the five path, was put to a ride in the three path midway around the turn, but faded form the five path in the stretch. DONTONIO always trailed around the two to three paths.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Aventura S. GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 88. Stakes Purse 65000. TWO YEAR OLDS. Free nomination by Sunday, September 10. $650 to enter. A $100 supplementary nomination may be made prior to closing time of entries. After payment of 1% to all owners of horses finishing sixth through last, 60% of the remaining purse shall be paid to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 5% to fourth and 3% to fifth.*(Not part of the announced gross purse, the FTBOA offers $25,000 to the owner of a registered Florida-bred finishing first, paid directly by FTBOA). Weight: 122 lbs. Non-winners of a race other than maiden or claiming allowed 2 lbs; a race other than claiming, 4 lbs. Starters to be named by usual time of closing. All fees shall be paid prior to the race. No Lasix Permitted Within 24 Hours of Post Time.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIVIETO was bumped hard on both sides at the start, set a clear pace in the two path, held clear to deep stretch and lasted. SECRET CHAT was slammed between foes at the start, raced off the pace down the backstretch, made good progress four wide around the turn, loomed three wide in upper stretch, could not gain on the winner for some time then steadily gained through the final sixteenth. SELF SUFFICIENT was bumped between foes at the start, raced in range two wide, continued on the left lead in the lane and finished evenly. BRAWN came out and bumped foes at the start, trailed inside to upper stretch and passed tiring rivals. JIVE came in and bumped the winner at the start, chased the pace two wide and faded after a half. DONTBESOOGROUCHY chased the pace three wide and four wide and retreated through the lane.
